<br>
Pierce Shades must now face:<br>
30% penalty vs Plate <br>
30% penalty vs Studded<br>
30% penalty vs Leather<br>
15% bonus vs Chain<br>
<br>
You can see why Pierce shades are crying foul on this one. Albion thrusters have less penalties by not having to face their own plate resistance, and reinforced has less thrust resistance than studded. Pierce Shades will have the most difficulty taking down Archers of other realms, all of which wear studded.<br>
<br>
So, should Shades respec to blades?<br>
<br>
Slash bonuses/penalties:<br>
20% penalty vs Plate<br>
30% penalty vs Chain<br>
20% penalty vs Studded<br>
15% bonus vs Leather<br>
<br>
Eouch, didn't see much improvement there. You can try to make a case that a bladeshade is designed to take out Assassins, but their natural stat and class abilities will continue to be sub par to Inf/Sbs. What really hosed Bladeshades is that they only have a bonus against Leather. Slash Infiltrators and All Shadowblades also now have a 15% damage bonus against Scale in addition to Leather, increasing their slash targets in relation to vs Assassins only in blades. A Nightshade will never get the benefit that Inf/SBs get through Slash.<br>
<br>
The blades situation affects all of Hibernia. Is it a problem for the tanks? No, they can be just as effective by specializing in Blunt which is starting to sound like the Hibernian thing to do, like Slash might be in the best interest of Midgard in some cases, works out for Shadowblades as well. Only problem for Nightshades? The weapon trend of the realm is not specializable, Nightshades cannot take up blunt. The best they can do us used unspecialized 2h staves.<br>
<br>
I didn't think it was possible to nerf Nightshades without nerfing Infiltrators or Shadowblades too, but Mythic shows it can be done. If you ever want to counter Infiltrators or Shadowblades, boost up Nightshades. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A> at: 7/25/02 4:38:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubrendelblackhammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brendel Blackhammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/02 6:27:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3793.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> NEW RESISTANCES</span><hr size=1> Everyone please look at my post above about the old resistances. Here is what the new resistances will look like, with the execption of scale. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Also please refrain from using the VN boards for information. Thats like saying &quot;I seen it on TV so it must be true&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
